FORMATION
OF
THE
GEOMAGNETIC
STORM
MAIN
PHASE
RING
CURRENT
THE
MAIN
PHASE
RING
CURRENT
IS
SUPPOSED
TO
BE
GENERATED
BY
HEATING
THE
EXOSPHERIC
GAS
BY
HYDROMAGNETIC
SHOCK
WAVES
THE
MORE
ENERGETIC
COMPONENT
CONSISTS
OF
PROTONS
A
FLUX
HYDROGEN
ATOMS
SHOULD
BE
OBSERVED
AT
THE
BASE
OF
THE
EXOSPHERE
AND
THE
DECAY
TIME
OF
THE
RING
SHOULD
BE
LESS
AT
SUNSPOT
MINIMUM
THAN
AT
SUNSPOT
MAXIMUM
BY
A
FACTOR
OF
THREE
